ğŸ³ Docker Setup

This project uses the following containers:

Jenkins Server

Runs on: localhost:8080

Auto-configured with Docker access

Mounts Terraform code and workspace

Terraform Runner

Based on official Terraform Docker image.

ğŸ§© docker-compose.yml
services:
  jenkins:
    image: jenkins/jenkins:lts
    container_name: jenkins-server
    user: root
    ports:
      - "8080:8080"
      - "50000:50000"
    volumes:
      - ./jenkins_home:/var/jenkins_home
      - /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock
      - ./terraform:/terraform

  terraform-runner:
    image: hashicorp/terraform:1.6
    container_name: terraform-runner
    volumes:
      - ./terraform:/workspace
    working_dir: /workspace


Start the environment:

docker-compose up -d

ğŸŒ Application

Simple HTML web app:

app/index.html


This file is copied into an Nginx container using Terraform.

ğŸŒ Terraform Infrastructure Code

Terraform deploys:

Docker image: nginx

Docker container: webapp

Volume mount: HTML file into container

Application is exposed at:

http://localhost:8085

ğŸ¤– Jenkins Pipeline Script

Pipeline performs:

Git Checkout

Terraform Init

Terraform Plan

Terraform Apply

Add this in Jenkins â†’ Pipeline â†’ Script:

pipeline {
  agent any

  stages {
    stage('Checkout') {
      steps {
        git 'https://github.com/openshift09/devops-portfolio-amith.git'
      }
    }

    stage('Init Terraform') {
      steps {
        sh 'terraform -chdir=terraform init'
      }
    }

    stage('Plan Terraform') {
      steps {
        sh 'terraform -chdir=terraform plan'
      }
    }

    stage('Apply Terraform') {
      steps {
        sh 'terraform -chdir=terraform apply -auto-approve'
      }
    }
  }
}

ğŸš¨ How CI/CD Works

Developer commits a change (HTML, Terraform, Jenkinsfile, etc.)

GitHub updates repo

Jenkins auto-pulls new changes

Jenkins triggers Terraform

Terraform deploys infrastructure

App is reachable on browser

